    "name": "COU1: Non-cannulated construct compression-bending prediction",
    "description": "FEA predicts construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw design under ASTM F1717 static compression-bending. Validated by direct comparison to bench testing (N=11 constructs across two laboratories). Model influence MEDIUM (testing confirms results); decision consequence MEDIUM (pedicle screw fracture leads to revision surgery, not death).",
    "intendedUse": "Demonstrate that the FEA modeling framework reproduces experimental compression-bending behavior of a non-cannulated pedicle screw construct within pre-established acceptance bounds (<10% QoI difference, E/uval < 1.96).",
    "modelInfluence": "Medium",
    "decisionConsequence": "Medium",
    "deviceClass": "Class II",
    "hasOperatingEnvelope": {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/cou/cou1-noncannulated/operating-envelope",
      "type": "OperatingEnvelope",
      "name": "ASTM F1717 compression-bending operating envelope for 7.5 mm non-cannulated pedicle screw",
      "description": "The model is validated within the following bounded operating conditions: axial compressive load 0–2500 N applied at 5 mm/min crosshead displacement rate; bending moment arm 60–80 mm per ASTM F1717 fixture geometry; screw outer diameter 7.3–7.7 mm (nominal 7.5 mm, machining tolerance ±0.2 mm); titanium alloy Ti-6Al-4V ELI with elastic modulus 110–114 GPa and yield strength 880–950 MPa; UHMWPE block density 0.93–0.95 g/cm³ representing vertebral body surrogate; test temperature 22 ± 3 °C; displacement range 0–45 mm. Predictions outside these bounds are not covered by this validation."
    },
    "hasApplicabilityConstraint": {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/cou/cou1-noncannulated/applicability-constraint",
      "type": "ApplicabilityConstraint",
      "name": "Applicability constraint: non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw, static loading only",
      "description": "This validation applies exclusively to non-cannulated pedicle screws with outer diameter 7.3–7.7 mm under quasi-static compression-bending per ASTM F1717. It does not extend to: (1) cannulated screw geometries; (2) dynamic or fatigue loading; (3) screw diameters outside 7.3–7.7 mm; (4) polyaxial or tulip-head configurations; (5) in vivo or cadaveric bone fixation. The FEA ensemble was validated against N=11 constructs spanning two independent laboratories; coverage of the full geometric tolerance band is acknowledged as sparse at the extremes (7.3 mm and 7.7 mm), and predictions at those boundary values carry higher uncertainty as documented in the uncertainty quantification record."
    }
  },
